President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring December 7th as National Pearl Harbor Remembrance Day in honor of the lives lost during the attack on Pearl Harbor in 1941. The proclamation pays tribute to the men, women, and children who lost their lives during the attack and recognizes the sacrifices made by service members today. It highlights the unity and resilience of the American people in the face of adversity and emphasizes the importance of upholding the ideals of liberty. The proclamation also encourages Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities and urges federal agencies and organizations to fly the flag at half-staff in honor of those who died at Pearl Harbor.